**Charts**

When displaying a chart in the UI, always include underlying table and query as tabs:

```python
chart_tab, table_tab, query_tab = st.tabs(["Chart","Table","Query"])
```

Use NBIM's color scheme described in src.viz_utils.py:
```python
{
    "midnight": "#001538",
    "accent blue": "#0026FF",
    "sanddark": "#D65218",
    "sea": "#4EC2E2",
    "emerald": "#3DD173",
    "pink": "#FF75DE",
    "violet": "#884DF7",
    "sky": "#F5F2EB",
    "grey": "#BFC3C9",
    "sand": "#F4CEA4",
    "polar": "#C3E9EE",
    "seadark": "#0A5877",
    "forrest": "#00755F",
    "lilac": "#AF9DFF",
}
```

Use streamlit subheading and a suitable caption instead of a title in the chart itself.